<h2>4.2 The <span class=3DSpellE>Three</span> Influence Types</h2>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'>Influence <span class=3D=
SpellE>relationships</span>
are <span class=3DSpellE>directional</span>, <span class=3DSpellE>typed</sp=
an>, and
carry a <span class=3DSpellE>semantic</span> <span class=3DSpellE>field</sp=
an>
(influence / <span class=3DSpellE>context</span> / cluster) <span class=3DS=
pellE>that</span>
<span class=3DSpellE>determines</span> <span class=3DSpellE>whether</span> =
<span
class=3DSpellE>they</span> <span class=3DSpellE>participate</span> in the <=
span
class=3DSpellE>exposure</span> propagation engine. Only <span class=3DSpell=
E><span
class=3DGramE>semantic</span></span><span class=3DGramE>:</span> influence =
<span
class=3DSpellE>relationships</span> <span class=3DSpellE>contribute</span> =
to <span
class=3DSpellE>exposure</span> <span class=3DSpellE>calculation</span> &#82=
12; <span
class=3DSpellE>context</span> and cluster <span class=3DSpellE>relationship=
s</span>
are traversable and <span class=3DSpellE>displayed</span> but carry no <span
class=3DSpellE>computational</span> <span class=3DSpellE>weight</span>.</p>

