>interconnected</span>
groups for portfolio-<span class=3DSpellE>level</span> <span class=3DSpellE=
>governance</span>).
All analyses are scope-<span class=3DSpellE>aware</span> <span class=3DSpel=
lE>with</span>
configurable <span class=3DSpellE>depth</span>.</p>

<h2>4.6 <span class=3DSpellE>Analysis</span> Scopes and the Path to <span
class=3DSpellE>SubGraphs</span></h2>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'>The scope system <span
class=3DSpellE>allows</span> <span class=3DSpellE>named</span> <span class=
=3DSpellE>subsets</span>
of <span class=3DSpellE>nodes</span> to <span class=3DSpellE>be</span> <span
class=3DSpellE>defined</span> and <span class=3DSpellE>analysed</span> <span
class=3DSpellE>independently</span>. A scope <span class=3DSpellE>behaves</=
span> as
if <span class=3DSpellE>it</span> <span class=3DSpellE>were</span> the <span
class=3DSpellE>entire</span> graph &#8212; all <span class=3DSpellE>statist=
ics</span>,
CRUD <span class=3DSpellE>operations</span>, <span class=3DSpellE>node</spa=
n> <span
class=3DSpellE>selection</span> <span class=3DSpellE>dropdowns</span>, <span
class=3DSpellE>exposure</span> <span class=3DSpellE>calculations</span>, an=
d <span
class=3DSpellE>analysis</span> <span class=3DSpellE>functions</span> respec=
t scope <span
class=3DSpellE>boundaries</span>. Partial scope-<span class=3DSpellE>awaren=
ess</span>
<span class=3DSpellE>is</span> <span class=3DSpellE>worse</span> <span
class=3DSpellE>than</span> no scope at all, <span class=3DSpellE>because</s=
pan> <span
class=3DSpellE>it</span> <span class=3DSpellE>produces</span> <span class=
=3DSpellE>silently</span>
incorrect <span class=3DSpellE>results</span>.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'>Scopes are the architect=
ural <span
